Subject: [PATCH] kbuild: generate .mod via $(file) not printf (qcacld/WiFi)

scripts/Makefile.build cmd_mod does
  printf '%s\n' $(real-search ...) | awk ... > $@
For a module with thousands of objects (qcacld-3.0 WiFi on aurora) the
$(real-search) expansion becomes a single argv string that exceeds the
kernel's MAX_ARG_STRLEN (128 KiB per argument) — /bin/sh rejects the
printf with "Argument list too long" (NOT ARG_MAX; ulimit -s does not
help). The module link itself already uses an @response-file, only the
.mod generation overflows. GNU make >= 4 provides the builtin
$(file >FILE,TEXT) which writes the list with no shell/argv limit;
write the object list with that and dedup with awk. Fixes the qcacld
build; harmless for all other modules. Device-specific build aid.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora qcacld build workaround for an
old kbuild; newer kbuild already avoids the giant argv]

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
--- a/scripts/Makefile.build
+++ b/scripts/Makefile.build
@@ -308,8 +308,12 @@
 	$(call if_changed,cc_lto_link_modules)
 endif
 
-cmd_mod = printf '%s\n' $(call real-search, $*.o, .o, -objs -y -m) | \
-	$(AWK) '!x[$$0]++ { print("$(obj)/"$$0) }' > $@
+# qcacld etc. have thousands of objects: `printf '%s\n' <list>`
+# exceeds the kernel MAX_ARG_STRLEN (128 KiB single argv string).
+# Write the list via GNU make's builtin $(file ...) (no shell/argv
+# limit) then dedup with awk. (Patched for aurora qcacld/WiFi.)
+cmd_mod = $(file >$@.tmp,$(call real-search, $*.o, .o, -objs -y -m)) \
+	$(AWK) '{ for (i = 1; i <= NF; i++) if (!x[$$i]++) print "$(obj)/" $$i }' $@.tmp > $@ && rm -f $@.tmp
 
 $(obj)/%.mod: FORCE
 	$(call if_changed,mod)
